	  <title>Parallel Hyperplanes - Examples</title>
	  <caption>Parallel Hyperplanes - Examples</caption>
	
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Determine if the solution hyperplanes of the equations below are parallel.</para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.array column="3">
            <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>x + 4y - 1z</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>1</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
            <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>2x - 8y - 2z</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>2</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </math.array>
		    </statement.showme>
		    <answer.showme type="Solution">
         <answer.showme.block>
            <answer.showme.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>We need to determine if the normal vectors of the two hyperplanes are parallel.</para.body>
               </para>
			            <ol>
				              <li>
					                <para>
                        <para.body>The first hyperplane has <math>
                              <latex>\Vect{u}:=(1,4,-1)</latex>
                           </math> as a normal vector.</para.body>
                     </para>
				              </li>
				              <li>
					                <para>
                        <para.body>The second hyperplane has <math>
                              <latex>\Vect{v}:=(2,-8,-2)</latex>
                           </math> as a normal vector.</para.body>
                     </para>
				              </li>
			            </ol>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>These vectors are parallel exactly when there exists a number <math>
                        <latex>t</latex>
                     </math> with</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.array column="3">
                  <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{v}</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>=</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>t\cdot \Vect{u}</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                  </row>
                  <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>\left[ \begin{array}{r} 2 \\ -8 \\ -2 \end{array} \right]</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>=</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>t\cdot \left[ \begin{array}{r} 1 \\ 4 \\ -1 \end{array} \right]</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                  </row>
               </math.array>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Comparing the first coordinates requires <math>
                        <latex>t=2</latex>
                     </math>, while comparing the second coordinates requires <math>
                        <latex>t=-2</latex>
                     </math>. This means that there is no number <math>
                        <latex>t</latex>
                     </math> with</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.array column="3">
                  <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{v}</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>=</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>t\cdot \Vect{u}</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                  </row>
               </math.array>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>So the normal vectors to the two hyperplanes are  not parallel and, therefore, the hyperplanes themselves are not parallel.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.showme.block.body>
         </answer.showme.block>
      </answer.showme>
	  </showme>
	
	
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para>
            <para.body>Determine if the solution hyperplanes of the equations below are parallel.</para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.array column="3">
            <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>3u + v - w + 2x</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>-1</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
            <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>2w - 6u - 2v - 4x</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>=</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
               <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                  <math>
                     <latex>\pi</latex>
                  </math>
               </cell>
            </row>
         </math.array>
		    </statement.showme>
		    <answer.showme type="Solution">
         <answer.showme.block>
            <answer.showme.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>We need to determine if the normal vectors of the two hyperplanes are parallel.</para.body>
               </para>
			            <ol>
				              <li>
					                <para>
                        <para.body>The first hyperplane has <math>
                              <latex>\Vect{v}:=(3,1,-1,2))</latex>
                           </math> as a normal vector.</para.body>
                     </para>
				              </li>
				              <li>
					                <para>
                        <para.body>The second hyperplane has <math>
                              <latex>\Vect{w}:=(-6,-2,2,-4)</latex>
                           </math> as a normal vector.</para.body>
                     </para>
				              </li>
			            </ol>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>We note that</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.array column="3">
                  <row xmlns:compositor="Compositor" compositor:rowspan="1">
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{w}</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>=</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>(-2)\cdot \Vect{v}</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                  </row>
               </math.array>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>So the normal vectors to the two hyperplanes are  parallel and, therefore, the hyperplanes themselves are parallel.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.showme.block.body>
         </answer.showme.block>
      </answer.showme>
	  </showme>
	
</showme.pack>
